A former Deputy National Chairman of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP), Senator Suleiman Nazif has been accused to be an anti-Northern sentiment and hawker of river dollars. The accusation was made by the National Chairman For Concern Northern PDP Alliance, Salaman Danladi Maianguwa in a statement, he signed and made available to Journalists in Bauchi. “In the midst of political permutations for various positions in Nigeria, politicians are eking desperate moves to ensure that their bread is buttered consistently and sufficiently, either through contesting for elective offices or merged as support group’. ” Those championing support groups are light-weight politicians with mirage hope of being elected into office, therefore forge alliances to invigorate their resurfacing to the political limelight” “The likes of Senator Nazif Suleiman Gamawa (former deputy National Chairman PDP) whose recent antics of championing the support group for The Executive Governor of Rivers State, Nyesom Wike, is to butter his bread against Northern sentiments” “The Senator against all odds, formulate a group of dysfunctional status, 0rganize fake appeal funds to purchase presidential Nomination and interest form of N40,000,000 for Nyesom Wike, the Executive Governor of Rivers state to contest the position of President of Federal Republic of Nigeria under Peoples Democratic Party” “The improvise support groups, Northern Progressive Element and Northern Conservative Forum for Wike under the leadership of Senator Nazif was a mare procreation of negativity and naivety, is a misplaced priority in the highest order”. “Taking into consideration the political history of Nazif whose first political breakthrough was in 2003, the then Vice President, Atiku Abubakar single-handedly influenced his election as House of Representatives members under Peoples Democratic Party” POLL “Having foreseen the dangers of his actions in PDP, he decamped to the ACN and contested the senatorial seat and became second runner up, the resignation of the candidate of ANPP (former Deputy Governor Abdulmalik Mahood) gave Nazif the legal opportunity to become Senator” ” Nazif in 2015, was later elected as Senator again under the wind-fall of APC, and returned to PDP in 2019, contested and lost the election, and in the company of Senator Bala Mohammed, Executive Governor of Bauchi State, he swindled the position of Deputy National Chairman of Peoples Democratic Party” The statement read in parts